#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn47.18"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.18:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.18:0.2"
msgid "2. Nālandavagga "
msgstr "2. At Nālandā "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.18:0.3"
msgid "18. Brahmasutta "
msgstr "18. With Brahmā "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn47.18:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā uruvelāyaṃ viharati najjā nerañjarāya tīre ajapālanigrodhe paṭhamābhisambuddho. "
msgstr "At one time, when he was first awakened, the Buddha was staying near Uruvelā at the goatherd’s banyan tree on the bank of the Nerañjarā River. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.18:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavato rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "Then as he was in private retreat this thought came to his mind, "

msgctxt "sn47.18:1.3"
msgid "“ekāyanvāyaṃ maggo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa sacchikiriyāya, yadidaṃ—cattāro satipaṭṭhānā. "
msgstr "“The four kinds of mindfulness meditation are the path to convergence. They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to end the cycle of suffering, and to realize extinguishment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn47.18:2.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

# NOTE: BB doesn’t capture the optative here. The Buddha is thinking of the practice his followers will take. In fact, BB’s text seems to follow the standard trope by mistake; it also adds “here” for idha, and omits vā.
msgctxt "sn47.18:2.2"
msgid "Kāye vā bhikkhu kāyānupassī vihareyya ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ; "
msgstr "A mendicant would meditate observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.18:2.3"
msgid "vedanāsu vā bhikkhu … pe … "
msgstr "Or they’d meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "sn47.18:2.4"
msgid "citte vā bhikkhu … pe … "
msgstr "or mind … "

msgctxt "sn47.18:2.5"
msgid "dhammesu vā bhikkhu dhammānupassī vihareyya ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "or principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.18:2.6"
msgid "Ekāyanvāyaṃ maggo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa sacchikiriyāya, yadidaṃ—cattāro satipaṭṭhānā”ti. "
msgstr "The four kinds of mindfulness meditation are the path to convergence. They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to end the cycle of suffering, and to realize extinguishment.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.168, sc3
msgctxt "sn47.18:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho brahmā sahampati bhagavato cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva kho brahmaloke antarahito bhagavato purato pāturahosi. "
msgstr "Then Brahmā Sahampati knew what the Buddha was thinking. As easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, he vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in front of the Buddha. "

msgctxt "sn47.18:3.2"
msgid "Atha kho brahmā sahampati ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.18:3.3"
msgid "“evametaṃ, bhagavā, evametaṃ, sugata. "
msgstr "“That’s so true, Blessed One! That’s so true, Holy One! "

msgctxt "sn47.18:3.4"
msgid "Ekāyanvāyaṃ, bhante, maggo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa sacchikiriyāya, yadidaṃ—cattāro satipaṭṭhānā. "
msgstr "Sir, the four kinds of mindfulness meditation are the path to convergence. They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to end the cycle of suffering, and to realize extinguishment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn47.18:4.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn47.18:4.2"
msgid "Kāye vā, bhante, bhikkhu kāyānupassī vihareyya ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ; "
msgstr "A mendicant would meditate observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.18:4.3"
msgid "vedanāsu vā, bhante, bhikkhu … pe … "
msgstr "Or they’d meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "sn47.18:4.4"
msgid "citte vā, bhante, bhikkhu … pe … "
msgstr "or mind … "

msgctxt "sn47.18:4.5"
msgid "dhammesu vā, bhante, bhikkhu dhammānupassī vihareyya ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "or principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.18:4.6"
msgid "Ekāyanvāyaṃ, bhante, maggo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā sokaparidevānaṃ samatikkamāya dukkhadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamāya ñāyassa adhigamāya nibbānassa sacchikiriyāya, yadidaṃ—cattāro satipaṭṭhānā”ti. "
msgstr "The four kinds of mindfulness meditation are the path to convergence. They are in order to purify sentient beings, to get past sorrow and crying, to make an end of pain and sadness, to end the cycle of suffering, and to realize extinguishment.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn47.18:5.1"
msgid "Idamavoca brahmā sahampati. "
msgstr "That’s what Brahmā Sahampati said. "

msgctxt "sn47.18:5.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvā athāparaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then he went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn47.18:6.1"
msgid "“Ekāyanaṃ jātikhayantadassī, "
msgstr "“The compassionate one, who sees the ending of rebirth, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.18:6.2"
msgid "Maggaṃ pajānāti hitānukampī; "
msgstr "understands the path to convergence. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.18:6.3"
msgid "Etena maggena tariṃsu pubbe, "
msgstr "By this path people crossed over before, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.18:6.4"
msgid "Tarissanti ye ca taranti oghan”ti. "
msgstr "will cross, and are crossing.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.18:6.5"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
